# Maintainer policy (agents)

Apply these defaults when proposing CI, release, or infrastructure changes.

## Use

- GitHub Actions, Issues, Projects, Pages, Releases
- Biome, Bun, Lefthook, Changesets, Turborepo (local cache)
- Dependabot, `bun audit`
- Public npm packages (`@quester/*`)
- Unsigned desktop builds on GitHub Releases
- GitHub Pages for docs and web

## Do not add

- Code signing pipelines or certificate dependencies
- Third-party coverage SaaS (Codecov, Coveralls, SonarCloud)
- Snyk, Socket.dev, Datadog, Sentry, or similar paid monitors
- npm private packages / Teams
- Vercel/Netlify Pro, Turbo Remote Cache, paid CI runners
- API keys or paid MCP integrations in the repository

## Public documentation rule

Never write budget, cost, or pricing rationale in README, CONTRIBUTING, SECURITY, ROADMAP, CHANGELOG, apps/docs, issues, or PR text. State technical policy only (e.g. "unsigned builds", "GitHub Pages hosting").

## CI efficiency

- Default CI to `ubuntu-latest` single job
- Release workflow: `workflow_dispatch` (manual trigger)
- Changesets version PR can be created locally if automation is heavy

## Cursor

- Run `bun run lint && bun run test` locally before agent commits
- Prefer focused package-scoped changes
